cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.DS

The paper discusses the use of machine learning methods for detecting non-technical losses in power grids, which falls under the category of data science and machine learning. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the issue of bias in the data, which is a common problem in computer security (cs.CR) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also presents a novel framework for quantifying and visualizing covariate shift, which could fall under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI) or data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
